.page-header
  %h1
    Orthography Tree
.row
  .col-xs-2
    %p.tree-expl
      Starting point is a
      %b
        Greek lemma
      in the middle of the first column.
  .col-xs-2
    %p.tree-expl
      In the second column, there are the corresponding
      %b
        coptic sublemmas.
      A colored rectangle highlights the part-of-speech:
      = succeed ', ' do
        %span.noun-color noun
      = succeed ', ' do
        %span.adjective-color adjective
      = succeed ', and' do
        %span.verb-color verb
      = succeed '.' do
        %span.adverb-color adverb
  .col-xs-2
    %p.tree-expl
      The
      %b
        orthographies
      are in the middle. Within each group, the entities are ordered by their dating descending.
  .col-xs-5
    %p.tree-expl
      On the right side, some information to the orthographies are depicted.
      The bars, end points of the links, show the
      %b
        frequency
      of an orthography.
      The
      %b
        dating
      âŒš is simplified to the mean when a period is given.
      For instance, a dating 400 to 499 is mapped to 450.
      The
      %b
        dialect
      ğŸ‘¤ defines the color of the bars
      = precede '(' do
        = succeed ', ' do
          %span.a-dialect-color A
      = succeed ', ' do
        %span.l-dialect-color L L* L4 L5 L6
      = succeed ',' do
        %span.s-dialect-color S Sp SR
      = succeed ', and' do
        %span.m-dialect-color M M4 M5
      = succeed ').' do
        %span.b-dialect-color B B4
      All other dialects are not specially highlighted.
      Eventually, one example
      %b
        manuscript
      ğŸ“„ for the dating-dialect paring is shown. All manuscripts can be retrieved by clicking on the text.

.row
  .panel.panel-default
    .panel-heading
      Browse an orthography tree
    .panel-body
      = collection_select :greek_lemma, :id, GreekLemma.all.order(:label), :id, :label, options = {include_blank: "Select a Greek lemma..."}, html_options = {:onchange => "loadData(this.value)"}
      %button{:onclick => "collapseAll()", :class => "btn btn-default"}
        Collapse it
      %button{:onclick => "expandAll()", :class => "btn btn-default"}
        Expand it
    #tree-container

